00:44:32.920 --> 00:44:33.920
&gt;&gt;Brad: I am sorry for not reading the book
first.

00:44:33.920 --> 00:44:34.920
&gt;&gt;Bill: about newspapers.

00:44:34.920 --> 00:44:36.430
So, if I can go back to the motion picture
one,

00:44:36.430 --> 00:44:44.480
um, motion picture companies certainly make
money off of licensing, and copyright

00:44:44.480 --> 00:44:47.420
is a significant part of that licensing.

00:44:47.420 --> 00:44:52.450
So there's secured interests and there's presells,
and there's regional agreements, so

00:44:52.450 --> 00:44:54.580
&gt;&gt;Brad: The story of George Lucas is quite
famous in that regard.

00:44:54.580 --> 00:44:55.580
&gt;&gt;Bill: Sure.

00:44:55.580 --> 00:45:00.220
So it does play a role in those things, I
will say, however, that the part about--

00:45:00.220 --> 00:45:02.950
that it still doesn't create value.

00:45:02.950 --> 00:45:05.840
That's another one of those intuitive things
that I don't think is true.

00:45:05.840 --> 00:45:10.000
No one's going to go to a lousy movie because
it's copyrighted.

00:45:10.000 --> 00:45:14.810
People are going to go to a great movie
because they think it's inherently great.

00:45:14.810 --> 00:45:17.030
&gt;&gt;Brad: But the idea of copyright is, if there
is value

00:45:17.030 --> 00:45:18.030
&gt;&gt;Bill: Right.

00:45:18.030 --> 00:45:19.030
&gt;&gt;Brad: Copyright lets you protect it.

00:45:19.030 --> 00:45:20.540
&gt;&gt;Bill: That's the free riding part, that's
the free riding part,right.

00:45:20.540 --> 00:45:23.320
So the mistake, however, I think, is that
copyright

00:45:23.320 --> 00:45:29.240
by itself creates value, whereas, at least
to me, it's the market and consumer demand

00:45:29.240 --> 00:45:33.250
that create value and copyright, as you
were pointing out, plays a role in creating

00:45:33.250 --> 00:45:35.840
it, once there.

00:45:35.840 --> 00:45:40.420
I think the mistake is that if I own a bunch
of copyrights, it's really valuable, and the

00:45:40.420 --> 00:45:44.440
mistake becomes important when it's a policy
issue, right?

00:45:44.440 --> 00:45:51.540
Now copyright can lead to greater competition,
and the knowledge economy is based upon competition,

00:45:51.540 --> 00:45:55.050
and knowledge economy needs copyright.

00:45:55.050 --> 00:45:59.290
Those sort of syllogism that aren't, that
aren't quite there.

00:45:59.290 --> 00:46:00.290
That's my only point.

00:46:00.290 --> 00:46:02.349
I certainly agree it's significant for licensing.

00:46:02.349 --> 00:46:04.510
&gt;&gt; Brad: To the, to the question of the news?

00:46:04.510 --> 00:46:12.250
&gt;&gt;Bill: Yeah, you know, I would say, the way
